# Documentation Guidelines

- All README files, feature usage guides, and project documentation must be written in Korean.
- Documentation should be clear, polite, and easy to understand for both users and developers.
- Code comments should be written in Korean with sufficient detail.
- Proper and up-to-date documentation is essential for project quality and maintainability.
- Avoid redundancy and ambiguity in documentation content.

